<br>
it would be a very cool idea, specially for those fights where the mob is MR/FR anyway. least you can open a nice can of whoopass on the badies <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
another way to do this would be a spell that blanks out your spell bar, gives you a 4000 point damage absorbtion shield, and gives you the skills of a earth elemental for the duration of the spell (augmented to double attack, and single wield) <br>
<br>
basicly it would work like the old shaman frenzy line, where you become a warrior until the damage shield is taken down by melee damage.<br>
<br>
call it, embody the elements or something <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odibillauxes>Odibil Lauxes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#333333>(1/4/03 6:40:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8338.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.thirdage.com/Games/odibil/odicon.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: not bad</span><hr size=1> It's a nice idea that I'm sure everyone would welcome, and technically a very easy process.<br>
<br>
The AA could easily turn you to the pet's perspective just as it would with an eye, allowing you only physical control over the pet. In order to control the pets attacks, the Mage would have to use the /pet attack and back off commands just as normal. All in all, you're just getting control over the placement of your pet.<br>
<br>
Just as with the eye, this process would hinder your characters physical movement, but would allow your character to cast spells and carry on otherwise as normal. The character and pet would not be able to move simultaneously, giving some balance for the power gained through the control of the pet, especially in PVP.<br>
<br>
To prevent possible exploiting, the skill would only have the same duration as the Eye of Tallon, with a reuse timer of 10 seconds from the initial use. Once the pet was out of a certain respectable range, it would be unable to be physically commanded, so that people don't use this skill as an eye with an unlimited timer.<br>
<br>
This is really the only way I can see this skill working realistically, and actually considered by the developers. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:tahoma,verdana;font-size:xx-small;">::: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Master</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> | <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=90407" target="top">Odibil Lauxes</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> | <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Arch Mage</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> :::<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->That which ordinary men are fit for, I am qualified in;<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->and within the best of me is <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.diligenceguild.com" target="top">DILIGENCE</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->.</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 718<br> <font color=#333333>(1/4/03 7:41:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8338.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: not bad</span><hr size=1> I really do like this idea. Though I did think of another potential complicating factor.<br>
